    <h3>29th January 2018</h3>
      <br>
      <p>Hello!</p> 

      <p>There are not many experiences more fulfilling than watching a mighty tree grow out of a tiny seed you’ve planted. </p>
         
      <p style="text-indent: 3em;">It’s been four days since we’ve landed in Ahemedabad and it’s been profoundly gratifying to contemplate the fruit of last year’s work. We learned upon our arrival that all the glasses we had purchased during Kassiopé’s previous eye camp have succesfully been distributed throughout the community. Furthermore, the autorefractometer (the machine donated by LeVisiologiste to help us carry out eye tests) which we had given to Manav Sadhna, had been used many times by various volunteer ophtalmologists/optometrists in order to carry out eye tests throughout different slums.</p>
        
      <p style="text-indent: 3em;">We received a heartwarming welcome from the Manav Sadhna comunity upon our arrival and have since started to pull all the required infrastructure together in order to start the project this week. <p>
      
      <p style="text-indent: 3em;">Our first optometrist is arriving tomorow night, and we will be carrying out our first cataract screenings as of Wednesday morning.
      We are planning to see 50 patients at the Tekro Community center (one of Manav Sadhna’s satelite community center’s) and if all goes well we will go on to another 70 patients the following days.</p>
        
      <p>More news will be coming soon! </p>
        
      <p>A heartfelt thank you for all the eyes that have been opened through your help,
      <br>The Kassiopé team</p>
